Four former Cordis Corp members na im dem sama out of federal charges wey relate to di Miami based company sale of pacemaker, plus conspiracy to hide pacemaker jibiti.

Jarrs for U.S. District Court for Miami, con clear Harold Hershhenson wey be executive vice president, John Pagans, wey be vice president before, and Stephen Vadas, and Dean Cipor for wey be engineer for Cordis.

Before dis year, Cordis wey be medical device, e don gree to plead guilty to felony, and misdemnor charges wey relate to pacemaker, and to pay government about $5.7 million in fine, and oder costs.

Cordis don sell im pacemaker operation two years ago to Telectronics Holding Ltd for Australia.

